sopher's final seminars at the Collège de France. Its provocative thesis returns Foucault's concept of biopower to its home in sexuality studies and places queer theory front and center in current biopolitical debates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aFoucault, Michel, -- 1926-1984. 0aFriendship -- Philosophy. 0aFriendshipxPhilosophy. 0aFriendship. 0aGay and lesbian studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aSociology : Social Movements. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143844001940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438440019423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438440019/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles